{"type":"message","id":"864619ad","parentId":"fe67dda5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:36:03.898Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vcoh0pjs3blx_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 143447\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Strategy (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Key finding: CFI compression experiment showed CFI alone loses 92.9% recall\r\n- New insight: Constant Format Problem - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n- Next experiment is defined: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). This is a concrete next step that would advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what I can do in this pulse:\r\n1. I could write the experiment script to test the hybrid scoring\r\n2. I could update the research document with the next experimental design\r\n3. I could set up the data collection needed\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create the experiment script or design document for the Hybrid CFI×Freq experiment. Let me create a concise experiment specification that can be run.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pattern, I should probably create a document that defines the experiment clearly, or I could modify the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md to include the next experimental protocol.\r\n\r\nLet me create a focused action - I'll add the next experimental design to the research document, making it ready to run.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts, and the hybrid scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) needs validation. The next concrete step is to design and specify the Hybrid CFI×Freq experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experimental protocol for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) as a new section in the research document, specifying the exact methodology to test whether this formula distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\" tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIÃ-Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) Ã- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** â€\" combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap â€\" they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND freq â‰¥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) Ã- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\nnew_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## EXPERIMENT: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring (Strategy C)\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n**Expected Scores**:\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 × 1.00 = 1.00 (FALSE POSITIVE) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 × 1.00 = 1.00 (FALSE POSITIVE) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 × 1.00 = 0.96 (CORRECT) |\r\n| \"temporal\" | 80 | 0.85 | 0.85 × 0.67 = 0.57 (GOOD) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 40 | 0.70 | 0.70 × 0.33 = 0.23 (GOOD) |\r\n| rare term | 3 | 0.30 | 0.30 × 0.025 = 0.0075 (CORRECTLY FILTERED) |\r\n\r\n**Methodology**:\r\n1. Collect 200 pulses (same dataset as CFI experiment)\r\n2. Compute CFI(T) and freq(T) for all tokens\r\n3. Calculate hybrid_score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n4. Compare against ground truth (manually labeled \"constant-format\" vs \"research\")\r\n5. Compute precision/recall vs binary threshold (CFI ≥ 0.5)\r\n\r\n**Success Metric**: Hybrid scoring achieves ≥90% recall while maintaining precision ≥60%.\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** â€\" combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap â€\" they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:35:07\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377363894}}
